    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Plain, cup-shaped molds, usually of copper or tin, in which one prepares a timbale, which is dish made of finely minced meat, fish, or other ingredients, cooked in a crust.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
